ss I use a parameterized test. JUnit is going to call it without arguments, which would cause a failure. Maybe I could annotate the helper class with `@Nested`, but that doesn't seem right either. I wonder if I could register a ParameterResolver via JUnit extension for the static `@Test`, though that might still lead to an invalid test.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_g7iQeZWltrelyxbloykB7gNL|fc_0682c849c8de8b1b016a25d12574c48197a54c7de831f1908c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15to18/1.77/build -type f | rg 'native.*args|args|config|json$|log$' | head -200"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3518, "output": 2810, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63160, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780863202629, "responseId": "resp_0682c849c8de8b1b016a25d0e347008197a9c58b6a96850b24"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_g7iQeZWltrelyxbloykB7gNL|fc_0682c849c8de8b1b016a25d12574c48197a54c7de831f1908c", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15to18/1.77/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\ntests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15to18/1.77/build/native/generated/generateTestResourcesConfigFile/resource-config.json\ntests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk15to18/1.77/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/bcutil-jdk15to18-1.77/reflection-calls.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780863270157}]}
